							<div class="post_wrapper author">
								<div id="about_the_author">
									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/hattiewilliams/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Hattie_Williams_-_Credit_Ollie_Grove_1_1-e1752088466101-100x100.jpg" width="100" height="100" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Hattie_Williams_-_Credit_Ollie_Grove_1_1-e1752088466101-300x300.jpg 2x" alt="Hattie Williams" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/hattiewilliams/">Hattie Williams</a></h6>
										Hattie Williams is the author of <em>Bitter Sweet</em>. She began pursuing a music career in her teens and toured Europe extensively, making three studio albums and working as a composer before finding her way to book publishing (quite by accident). She spent the next twelve years working with some of the biggest authors in the world, and she is the former producer of the Iceland Noir Literary Festival, which takes place in Reykjavík every November. Williams continues to feed her creativity through her writing from her home in East London, where she lives with her partner and daughter.																			</div>
								</div><br class="clear"/><br/>
							</div>
							<br class="clear"/>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div>
													<div class="sidebar_content ad_bottom">
								<li id="custom_ads-24" class="widget Custom_Ads"><div class="htlad-LH_PP_F"></div></li>
							</div>
